Mark II | Long Haul Kayaks













































 


























Select Page


  
 



 



 











 





The Mark II 

The World's Most Rugged And Beautiful Folding Kayak 

 


 



 
 
 
 



The Mark II
 









Durable, reliable, and versatile. Our most popular model, the Mark II is time tested and tough with a life expectancy lasting decades. This model is the most versatile of any of our designs: tandem or solo paddling, fishing, sailing, day trips or long expeditions. The Mark II offers stability in the roughest conditions and for beginner paddlers. From the local lake, to the Florida Everglades, to the fjords of Norway, to the icy waters around Antarctica, the Mark II can take you there.
 
 
 


Boat Specs:
Weight: Classic 77 lbs / 35 kg | Expedition 86 lbs / 39 kg | Quattro 91 lbs / 41 kg
Length: 204″ / 518 cm
Beam: 36″ / 91 cm
Capacity: Classic & Expedition 800 lbs / 363 kg | Quattro 900 lbs / 408 kg
Cockpit: 17″ x 87″
Pack Size: 2 bags
 
 

Features:
The Mark II features our craftsman built ash and birch frame dipped in four coats of sealer and varnish to provide a beautiful, hard and long lasting finish. The hull is mad of the finest black Hypalon rubber, a time tested product whose strength and durability are legendary. The center rib of the Mark II, rib #4, is structurally engineered for strength and is the location of the rudder pedal mount.
You may choose a fabric deck of either our cotton (blue, red, olive, mint, or black) or the SeaMark material, (blue, red, burgundy, forest green or black).
 
Customize:
All hulls are tailored to your specs. Some of the custom features available include: lifeline, extra D-rings, tie-downs, full set keep strips, bow and/or stern oval deck hatch, Zippered loading deck hatch bow and/or stern.
 
 
 
 



